<br>
I thought (read in the interview on this site), that you can wield a weapon (if one of its req. is martial arts) and do special attacks at the same time.<br>
Well I just tried, but it doesn't work.<br>
<br>
My stats:<br>
Level 41<br>
Martial arts 290<br>
weapon: Rusty Hand Blade (martial arts 55 + some other)<br>
<br>
Anyone can help?<br>
<br>
Jodowein <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/ucreode.showPublicProfile?language=EN>creode</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Tiny Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 31<br> <font color=#660000>(9/9/01 8:41:50 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=263.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Martial Arts req. weapon and special attacks?</span><hr size=1> You can't use special attacks and weapons at the same time.  the COM did this so MA's have to choose between weapons and special attacks. (one of the requirements on special attacks is &quot;cannot wield weapons&quot;) <br>
<br>
I used to use 2 handblades but after the 12.5 patch they upped the damage of the special attacks, and I couldn't use them.  Switching in and out 2 handblades takes too long to be effective.  So I rerolled! 3rd time <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  And this time, if I use any weapons at all, I am gonna use a G-staff.<br>
<br>
First off, it's only one weapon, therefore easier to switch in and out.  <br>
<br>
Secondly, using 2 handblades I had NO IP left.  raising 1H edge, sneak attack, fast attack, and mult melee is too much, esp because they are all blue skills (mult melee and sneak attack are dark blue).  Using a g-staff only requires 2H blunt, fast attack, and sneak attack.  yay!  Plus, contrary to most of this board, I like using weapons <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Thirdly(??), the time special attacks lock MA skill goes up thru the lvls, so equipping and unequipping mid-fight won't happen as often, thus less of a pain in my ass! = good. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#99CC66><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/ucyjax.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cyjax</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Tiny Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 43<br> <font color=#660000>(9/9/01 1:37:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=263.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Martial Arts req. weapon and special attacks?</span><hr size=1> I have another one for you.  Try using a Merchant Blade or Whing for a weap.  You have to use 2hs, though.  Merchant blade only has 2hs and fast attack as extra skills (plus you can Brawl and Dimach holding it), but has a equip time of 3.5 seconds.  Whings have Piercing as an extra attack skill, but it has the same skills as Merchang blades and only a .5 equip time.<br>
<br>
Right now I am using Whings.  That .5 equip time rules for my ability to switch the weap in and out to be using my high level BoP.  Plus it just seems to recycle faster. I wonder if there is an extra attack in there or something that comes from the Piercing skill.  I will have to test this some more.<br>
